<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67a5feb-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7301"><num value="7301">§ 7301.</num><heading> General</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf67a5fec-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7301/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><chapeau> In this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf67a5fed-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7301/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> “service on deck” means service in the deck department in work related to the work usually performed on board vessels by able seamen and may include service on fishing, fish processing, fish tender vessels and on public vessels of the United States;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf67a5fee-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7301/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> 360 days is equal to one year’s service; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf67a5fef-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7301/a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> a day is equal to 8 hours of labor or duty.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf67a5ff0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7301/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The Secretary may prescribe regulations to carry out this chapter.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf67a5ff1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/541">97 Stat. 541</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/98/364/tIV/s402/9/B">Pub. L. 98–364, title IV, § 402(9)(B)</ref>, <date date="1984-07-17">July 17, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/448">98 Stat. 448</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
